title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_SSSpamTicketSeller
tags:
---
<<declare $playerName = "Player">>
<<declare $hatedFood = "Apple">>
<<declare $familiar = "Familiar">>
<<if $chapter2_SaltMireCity_Matthias_PlayerWins == 0>> 
    Player: Hi, can I have a single ticket please?
    Ticket Seller: Ah, my apologies. 
    Ticket Seller: With the Gantoh train being out of service, I'm afraid tickets for the next voyage are all sold out. 
    Player: What!? Sold out?
    Ticket Seller: Wait, I can see you have an adventurer's amulet. 
    Ticket Seller: There are still a few golden tickets to be won.
    Player: What's a golden ticket?
    Ticket Seller: Oh, it's an excellent prize. 
    Ticket Seller: Not only will it get you a place on this voyage but you'll also get to dine at the Captain's table. A very prestigious prize indeed!
    Player: How do I win one?
    Ticket Seller: By beating the Salt Mire City Guild Master, Matthias. 
    Ticket Seller: I hear he's pretty tough... and handsome.
        -> Player: Okay... Thanks for the information. I'll be heading to the Guild Hall anyway.
        -> Player: Whatever. Thanks I guess.
    Ticket Seller: Goodbye and thank you for your custom!
<<endif>>
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_HealingChurch_Roy
tags:
---
Roy: Oh! Hi {$playerName}. Let me heal your Familiar up for you.
Player: Roy? What are you doing here?
Roy: Oh...
Roy: After speaking to you back in Powder Town, I decided to pack up and try to pursue my dream after all. 
Roy: I'm staying with my cousin Sheila who works at the Familiar Nursery here.
    -> Player: That's amazing! 
    -> Player: This is your dream?
Roy: Well, it's the first step anyway. 
Roy: One day, I want to become a Bishop and open my own Healing Church. 
Roy: I'm not a noble and don't have much money. So to do that, I'd have to get letters of recommendation from the Healing Churches across Gantoh. 
Roy: I managed to pluck up the courage to get one from Powder Town and head here. 
Roy: I even bought a golden ticket to Omen City on the SS Spam but...
    -> Player: You can do it, Roy!
        Roy: Y-you really think so?
            -> Player: For sure. I've never seen someone heal Familiars as good as you.
                Roy: You're really kind, {$playerName}. I-
                Healers: *whispering*
                Roy: ...
                Player: What are they gossiping about?
                Roy: ...
                Roy: You should probably go... 
                Roy: I'll see you in Omen City, right?
                <<if $chapter2_SaltMireCity_Matthias_PlayerWins == 0>> 
                    Player: I'll see you on the SS Spam if I can get a ticket.
                <<endif>>  
                <<if $chapter2_SaltMireCity_Matthias_PlayerWins == 1>> 
                    Player: I have a ticket for the SS Spam too. I'll see you there!
                <<endif>>  
                Roy: That's great! 
                Healers: *whispering*
                Roy: ...
                Roy: I don't feel so good...
                Player: Roy? Are you alright?
                Roy: Bye, {$playerName}. I'll see you soon.
            ->Player: Maybe you aren't cut out for this.
                Roy: Yeah... you're probably right. I just thought...
                Healers: *whispering*
                Roy: ...
                Roy: I don't feel so good...
    -> Player: That's a stupid dream. 
        Player: I'm not sure why you're bothering with something like that.
        Roy: Do you really think so? 
        Healers: *whispering*
        Roy: ...
        Roy: I don't feel so good...
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_FamiliarNursery_Sheila1
tags:
---
Sheila: Ugh... 
Sheila: No, Mab... 
Sheila: Don't nibble Lady Lucaria's fingers...
Player: Erm... Hello?
Sheila: Gah! 
Sheila: Sheila at Salt Mire City Familiar Nursery at your service! What kind of Familiar are you after today?
Player: Were you sleeping?
Sheila: Don't tell the Head Breeder, please! 
Sheila: To tell you the truth, I'm bored stiff here. 
Sheila: People around here only want Familiars for industry or housework... pulling carts, helping with fishing, tending to crops. 
Sheila: No one is remotely interested in how they look!
Player: How they look?
Sheila: Yes! You know, like whether they have signs of good breeding. I mean...
Sheila: Wait. What's your name again?
Player: {$playerName}.
Sheila: {$playerName}, see my Queen Mab here? What do you think of her?
    -> Player: She's cute!
        Sheila: Exactly! Can you imagine her getting dirty doing manual labour? 
        Sheila: She's the result of all my hard work here... Err, in my free time, of course...
    -> Player: She doesn't look very industrious.
        Sheila: I should hope not! 
        Sheila: It took me years to breed one as fine as she. 
        Sheila: And what recognition does she get in a place like this? None!
Sheila: She could even win Crusts, I tell you!
Player: Crusts?
Sheila: The annual Familiar beauty contest in the Capital, Avaelon. 
Sheila: The first qualifier contest is in a few days in Omen City. 
<<if $Roy_Activated == 1>> 
    Sheila: My cousin, Roy, recently came to visit and bought a ticket for the SS Spam. 
    Sheila: He said he'd met someone who had inspired him to follow his dreams. 
    Sheila: I got all caught up in it and agreed to go with him. 
<<endif>>  
<<if $Roy_Activated == 0>> 
    Sheila: I got myself all worked up and bought a ticket for the SS Spam.
<<endif>>  
Sheila: I even spent most of my savings on upgrading my ticket for the SS Spam when I heard Lady Lucaria was going to be on the ship. But now I'm having second thoughts...
Sheila: What do you think I should do?
    -> Player: You should go. You and Queen Mab have got this!
        Sheila: You're right! We can do this! 
        Sheila: Thanks {$playerName}.
    -> Player: I think you should sell your ticket before you embarrass yourself.
        Sheila: ...
        Sheila: Sorry, Mab. I think I made a mistake.
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_FamiliarNursery_Sheila2
tags:
---
Sheila: I still haven't sold my ticket...
    -> Player: I think you should enter the Omen City contest after all.
        Sheila: Really? 
        Sheila: You're right! We can do this! T
        Sheila: Thanks {$playerName}.
    -> Player: You should.
        Sheila: I know. I will...
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_Inn
tags:
---
Innkeeper: Hello! Oh, another Adventurer? 
Innkeeper: You'll be wanting a room. You can have the one upstairs on the right.
    -> Player: Thank you.
        Innkeeper: Now that's refreshing! 
        Innkeeper: I was getting worried that Adventurers had begun to lose their manners. 
        Innkeeper: Just a few hours ago, I had a red-haired noble insult my establishment and wave around a golden ticket for the SS Spam like it made them royalty or something. Tch!
    -> Player: I want the best you have.
        Innkeeper: You and everyone else! 
        Innkeeper: Just earlier, I had a red-haired noble insult my establishment and wave around a golden ticket for the SS Spam like it made them royalty or something. Tch!
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_Timmy1
tags:
---
Timmy: Oh, hey buddy!
    -> Player: Hi, Timmy. How are you doing?
        Timmy: I'm good, thanks. Better now I've had a pint. 
        Timmy: Speaking of pints, I owe you a drink!
    -> Player: You're the hot-head who attacked me over a shiny pebble!
        Timmy: Hey, hey! I said I was sorry, didn't I? 
        Timmy: Come on, I owe you a drink.
<<jump chapter2_SaltMireCity_Timmy2>>
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_Timmy2
tags:
---
-> (Drink with Timmy.)
    Timmy: Here you go! Hands drink.
    Timmy: I realised I'd never asked your name.
    Player: Oh, I'm {$playerName}.
    Timmy: I have an interesting question for you {$playerName}, now that we've patched things over. 
    Timmy: How do you feel about bug-like Familiars?
        -> Player: It depends. They can be cute or creepy.
            Timmy: HA! You're right, there! 
            Timmy: That's why I love them so much. 
            Timmy: When I got a bit over-excited over that rock, I thought I might have found a fossil of one.
            Timmy: Fossils are easier to keep stashed in my pockets than live Familiars. HA! HA!
            Player: Yeah, I get that. 
            Player: Fossils must be hard to find, though? 
            Player: I don't think I've ever seen one.
            Timmy: Well, the Wilds are the best place to look. 
            Timmy: I haven't had much success yet but I hear a few have been found in the Omen Arrowroot Wilds recently. 
            Timmy: I'm headed there next. 
            Timmy: I'm after one fossil in particular. A really rare one! 
            Timmy: So if you hear of any other good fossil spots, then let me know, buddy!
            Player: Sure, I'll let you know, Timmy. 
            Player: See you later!
        -> Player: I want to squish them.
            Timmy: AGH! How could you say that? They're the best! 
            Timmy: Well, look here, buddy. 
            Timmy: I'm looking for some fossils of them in the Wilds. You can't squish fossils...
            Timmy: I'm heading to the Omen Arrowroot Wilds next to search there. 
            Timmy: I'm after one fossil in particular. A really rare one! 
            Timmy: So if you hear of any other good spots, then let me know, buddy!
            Player: Okay. If you insist, Timmy.
-> (Walk away.)
    Timmy: Hey! No hard feelings, right? 
    Timmy: At least let me know your name?
    Player: It's {$playerName}. 
    Player: You can keep your drink, Timmy.
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_GuildHall
tags:
---
Clerk: Greetings, Adventurer! 
Clerk: This is your first time in a Guild Hall, right? 
Player: How did you know?
Clerk: You can always tell. 
Clerk: The innocent, lost aura... The bright glint in their eyes...
Clerk: Anyway, this is where you can challenge the Guild Master and their acolytes. 
Clerk: You have to beat the acolytes first before you can take on Matthias. 
Clerk: This Guild Hall is all about the water element.
Clerk: The other thing you can do here is collect your allowance from the King. 
Clerk: This is for subduing wild Familiars and keeping the Gantoh Kingdom safe. 
Clerk: The higher your amulet rank, the more money you get. 
Clerk: You can check out the rates on the notice board over there.
Clerk: So, what would you like to do today?
    -> Player: Take on the Salt Mire City Guild Master, Matthias.
        Clerk: Okay. You can now proceed through the door up ahead when you're ready. 
        Clerk: Good luck! 
    -> Player: Collect my allowance.
         <<if $PlayerMoney == 0>> 
            Clerk: Looks like you haven't earned any money yet. 
            Clerk: Best get out there and subdue some wild Familiars.
         <<endif>>
        <<if $PlayerMoney > 0>> 
            Clerk: No problem. Here you go.
        <<endif>>
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_Matthias
tags:
---
Matthias: Hi, there! 
Matthias: I'm Matthias, the Guild Hall leader here. 
Matthias: Have you come to challenge me?
Player: Yes. I'm {$playerName}, from Brackenberry Village. 
Player: Professor Olivia is my sponsor.
Matthias: Professor Olivia? That's the third time I've heard that name recently. 
Matthias: The other two were pretty strong, so I have high hopes for you, {$playerName}!
Matthias: If you can defeat me, then you'll move up from brass to copper rank. 
Matthias: But I'm getting ahead of myself. 
Matthias: Come. Let's see what you can do.
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_Matthias_PlayerLoses
tags:
---
Matthias: Don't give up yet! 
Matthias: I saw signs of potential in you. 
Matthias: Promise me you'll come back for another try when you're ready?
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_Matthias_PlayerWins
tags:
---
Matthias: Just as I thought! 
Matthias: The bond between you and your Familiar is strong already. Unusually so. 
Matthias: Yes, I have faith that you will go far in your Adventuring journey, {$playerName}. 
Matthias: Congratulations on reaching Copper Rank!
Player: Thank you. 
Player: What about the golden tickets for the SS Spam? I heard you were giving some away.
Matthias: You're in luck. I have one last golden ticket here. 
Matthias: The ship is leaving for Omen City tomorrow morning. 
Matthias: I'll actually be travelling on the boat too!
    -> Player: You're leaving Salt Mire City?
    -> Player: Oh... Why?
Matthias: I have something I need to sort out. 
Matthias: It's something I should have really done some time ago but it cannot wait any longer. 
Matthias: It's partly in my capacity as a Guild Master and Royal Council Member. 
Player: What's the other part?
Matthias: ...
Matthias: Do you believe in legends, {$playerName}?
    -> Player: Of course!
        Matthias: I had a good feeling about you the moment you stepped into this room! 
        Matthias: Look for me when you're in Omen City. I have something interesting I'd like to show you.
    -> Player: They're nothing more than fairytales. 
        Matthias: Hmmm... That's disappointing to hear. 
        Matthias: Remember, all fairytales come from something. 
        Matthias: If you change your mind, seek me out in Omen City and we can continue this discussion.
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_Kenny1
tags:
---
Guard: So what did you see, ma'am?
Old Woman: Chaffy and I were just sitting in our usual spot, people watching in the town square, when we saw someone lurking.
Guard: Lurking?
Old Woman: Yes, lurking! 
Old Woman: They were very suspicious-looking. 
Guard: Do you have any details that might identify them?
Old Woman: Oh, my memory isn't what it used to be, sonny! 
Old Woman: They were kind of tall... I think? 
Old Woman: Or were they short? 
Old Woman: Maybe average-height?
Guard: Never mind. 
Guard: I'll see what I can do with your... information. 
Guard: Do you have anything to add to this report or are you simply eavesdropping?
    -> Player: Erm, no. Sorry. I was just curious.
    -> Player: Nothing at all.
Guard: Then be on your way, Adventurer. This is official business.
Old Woman: Hey, sonny. What's your name?
Guard: Kenny. 
Guard: Kenny, ma'am.
Old Woman: You look different to the usual city guards. 
Old Woman: Where do you come from?
Kenny: I must be on my way. 
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_Anne
tags:
---
Player: Anne?
<<if $Agreed_Help_Anne == 1 and $Pulled_Lever == 1>>
    Anne: Hi, {$playerName}! Good to see you made it. 
    Anne: Thanks for helping me back there. 
    Anne: I was hoping we would meet again. I always believe you should always treat your investors well.
    Player: Investors?
    Anne: A good deed is an investment in another person, is it not? 
    Anne: I'd like to offer you a permanent discount on all my stock. 
    Anne: You'll not find bargains like this anywhere else!
        -> Player: Wow, thanks!
            Anne: No problem. 
        -> Player: Oh, okay.
            Anne: A little bit of an underwhelming response there, {$playerName}. 
        Anne: Anyway, feel free to have a look at my cart and see if there's anything you like.
<<endif>>
<<if $Agreed_Help_Anne == 0 and $Pulled_Lever == 1>>
    Anne: Hi, {$playerName}. Fancy seeing you around here. 
    Anne: I'm glad you changed your mind and decided to help me after all. 
    Anne: I was hoping we would meet again. I always believe you should always reward good business sense.
    Player: Business sense?
    Anne: You know, natural instincts that seek out good deals and fortuitous exchanges? 
    Anne: For pulling that lever, I'd like to give you a free healing potion.
        -> Player: Wow, thanks!
            Anne: No problem. 
        -> Player: Oh, okay.
            Anne: Don't look a gift horse... or potion... in the mouth, {$playerName}. 
    Anne: Anyway, feel free to have a look at my cart and see if there's anything you like.
<<endif>>
<<if $Agreed_Help_Anne == 0 and $Pulled_Lever == 0>>
    Anne: You!
    Anne: Bet you didn't expect to see me here after leaving me to fend for myself in the Wilds, did you? 
    Anne: I lost a good portion of my stock trying to move that mining cart out of the way.
        -> Player: I'm really sorry. I shouldn't have done that.
            Anne: No, you shouldn't. 
            Anne: But... I can probably forgive you, if you become a regular customer of mine.
        -> Player: I'd do it again. It was funny.
            Anne: You're a proper piece of work, aren't you?
    Anne: Well… You can still take a look at my cart and see if there's anything you like.
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_Kenny2
tags:
---
Woman: Help! They stole my Familiar!
Kenny: You, there! 
Kenny: Stop them!
    -> Player: (Stop them.)
        Player: Unhand that Familiar!
        Team StopIt Grunt: Playing at being a Good Samaritan are you? Get out of my way!
    -> Player: (Do Nothing.)
        Kenny: What is wrong with you!? You just let them past!?
        Kenny: What is your name?
        Player: {$playerName}.
        Kenny: {$playerName}, next time, you should think about actually helping people in need instead of just standing there! 
        Kenny: Now move. 
        Kenny: I need to chase this villain down before they escape with this poor woman's Familiar and she never sees it again.
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_Kenny2_PlayerLoses
tags:
---
StopIt! Militia Grunt: Ha! Your Familiar is mine!
===

title: chapter2_SaltMireCity_Kenny2_PlayerWins
tags:
---
StopIt! Militia Grunt: Curses upon you all! 
StopIt! Militia Grunt: The StopIt! Militia will free all Familiars from your evil clutches!
Kenny: Good work... Erm...?
Player: {$playerName}.
Kenny: I'll return this Familiar to its owner and take this villain straight to the City Gaol for questioning.
Kenny: Unfortunately, I won't be able to do it myself. I need to be on my way at once. 
Player: What for?
Kenny: ...
Kenny: That's classified.
    -> Player: You're not a Salt Mire City guard, are you?
        Kenny: Of course I am.
    -> Player: ...
        Kenny: ...
        Kenny: Thanks again for helping keep the streets safe, {$playerName}.
===

title: chapter2_SSSpam_Intro
tags:
---
Butler: You seem a bit... different to our usual clientele. 
Butler: May I ask where you are from?
    -> Player: Brackenberry Village.
    -> Player: Nope.
Butler: I see...
Butler: It's clearly your first time aboard a luxury vessel. 
Butler: Well, you should feel privileged to have some very esteemed neighbours. 
Butler: A noble from the Sullivan family is residing in the cabin next door. One of the twins I do believe. 
Butler: This is your cabin. 
Butler: As a Golden Ticket holder, you have some free time to wander about before the bell rings for lunch at the Captain' table. 
Butler: Make sure you come back here to spruce yourself up beforehand. 
Butler: You don't want to make everyone feel uncomfortable, especially since it must have cost you dearly to purchase such a ticket.
Butler: Enjoy.
Player: Wow… I hate to admit it, but this is really nice. 
Player: I wonder how much this cabin would have normally cost?
Player: That snooty butler said I had some time to explore before lunch. I should make the most of it.
===

title: chapter2_SSSpam_Roy_and_Sheila
tags:
---
Roy: Hi, {$playerName}! 
Roy: Are you enjoying the trip so far?
Sheila: You know {$playerName} too, Roy?
Roy: Yeah! We met in Powder Town. 
Roy: They're the one who... Erm...
Sheila: Oh! That's so funny. 
Sheila: {$playerName} was the one who convinced me to enter the Omen City contest too!
But {$playerName}, have you seen Lady Lucaria yet?
Player: Who?
Sheila: Gah! Please tell me you're joking?
Roy: Lady Lucaria and her Familiar, Luxo, are famous Crusts winners. My cousin is quite obsessed with them.
Sheila: And so I should be! 
Sheila: The grace, the poise, the beauty! 
Sheila: Queen Mab and I would give almost anything to meet her... but I have no idea where she is.
Roy: Please don't leave me here by myself, Sheila.
Sheila: Fine…
    -> Player: I'll keep you company if you'd like, Roy?
        Roy: Really?! 
        Roy: I mean, please don't inconvenience yourself on my account! 
        Roy: I wouldn't want to hold you back. 
        Roy: I need to psyche myself up for lunch at the Captain's table anyway...
    -> Player: I'll keep an eye out for Lady Lucaria, Sheila.
        Sheila: Yay! 
        Sheila: If you spot her, give Mab a signal and we'll be right over. 
        Sheila: I'll drag Roy with us if I have to!
===

title: chapter2_SSSpam_Roy_No_Sheila
tags:
---
Roy: Hi, {$playerName}! 
Roy: Are you enjoying the trip so far?
    -> Player: It's amazing. 
        Player: Are you dining with the Captain, too?
        Roy: Yeah. I mean, I'm a bit nervous. 
        Roy: I'm a bit awkward around groups of strangers.
    -> Player: It's a bit poncy, isn't it?
        Roy: Haha, yeah! 
        Roy: I wouldn't have bought a Golden Ticket if it hadn't been the only type left. 
        Roy: I just really wanted to get to Omen City as quickly as possible before I had time to make myself too anxious about it.
===

title: chapter2_SSSpam_Sheila_No_Roy
tags:
---
Sheila: Hi {$playerName}, have you seen Lady Lucaria yet?
Player: Who?
Sheila: Gah! Please tell me you're joking?
Sheila: Lady Lucaria and her Familiar, Luxo, are famous Crusts winners!
Sheila: They excel in everything! Grace, poise, beauty! 
Sheila: Queen Mab and I would give almost anything to meet her... but I have no idea where she is.
    -> Player: I'll let you know if I see her. 
        Player: What is she like?
        Sheila: She's beautiful, a winner on every level! 
        Sheila: If you see her, give Mab a signal and we'll run over.
    -> Player: Let me know if you see her. 
        Player: I'm curious.
        Sheila: And so you should be! 
        Sheila: She's won several Crusts finals with Luxo, you know. 
        Sheila: She's a real celebrity!
===

