title: chapter2_SSSpam_Date_George
tags:
---
George: And this is the Dance Hall. 
George: Many nobles come here for entertainment, obviously. 
George: We'd better not get any closer or they'll think we want to join in. 
George: I'm sure that would be pretty embarrassing for you, since you wouldn't know any of the steps.
Player: I know the steps.
George: You have to be joking? 
George: Where did someone like you learn dance steps like those?
Player: My Dad taught me. 
Player: Us poor people do sometimes pick up some things from being around you nobles, you know.
George: Pfft, a likely story. 
Player: I'm telling the truth, George. 
Player: In fact, I probably know those steps better than you.
George: As if! 
George: Wait… I have an idea. 
George: I'll give you one last chance to retract that outrageous statement.
George: Or are you willing to prove it, little mouse?
    -> Player: You first, my Lord.
        George: W-what? Are you sure? 
        George: Well, I suppose it will be hilarious to watch you fall on your face.
        George: ...
        George: I can't believe it... You're actually good?
        Player: Thanks for the compliment.
        George: That wasn't a... Ugh! You're so irritating. 
        George: Let's see if you can keep up with me if I pull out the even more advanced version of this dance!
            -> Player: (Perform the steps flawlessy, just like Dad taught you.)
                George: This must be some sort of twisted nightmare. 
                George: Even Gigi doesn't dance this well!
            -> Player: (Stamp on his foot.)
                George: Ouch! 
                George: What was that for?
        George: Right, see if you can handle this spin! 
        Player: Ooof!
        George: Agh!
        Player: Erm... We're a bit close...
        George: Ugh, you're right! 
        George: You should be grateful that I caught you after you tripped.
        Player: You were the one who tripped! 
        Player: You would've fallen if you hadn't grabbed onto me.
        George: In your dreams.
        George: Looks like the dance is over. 
        George: That was kind of fun. 
        George: Er, I mean, funny watching you try to compete!
        George: ...
        George: Let's head back before your stupid tour makes me miss the next course.
    -> Player: On second thought, maybe I don't actually know the steps that well.
        George: Ha! I thought so. 
        George: Let's head back before your little tour makes me miss the next course.
===

