title: chapter2_SSSpam_StopItMilitia_Damien_or_Eliza
tags:
---
<<if $DamienElizaNowayIdontwanttogetcaughtupinthis== "No way">>
Player: ~ If they're going to kidnap Familiars, they'll need access to boats to escape. 
Player: ~ I should run to the deck and try to stop them.
<<endif>>
<<if $DamienElizaNowayIdontwanttogetcaughtupinthis == "I don't want to">>
Player: ~ If they're going to kidnap Familiars, they'll be occupied.
Player: ~ I should try to avoid them and run to my cabin as quickly as possible.
<<endif>>
Regiment Leader: You, stop right there! 
Regiment Leader: What are you doing, little Adventurer, here all alone?
Grunt: Crush them, boss.
Grunt 1: Yeah, let's show them what happens to those who resist us.
Grunt 2: We have some of the Familiar crew. 
Grunt 2: We still need to find the Captain, Lady Lucaria and take some of the nobles' Familiars.
Grunt 1: Yeah, make this quick so we can take them all!
Regiment Leader: What do you have to say to all that, Adventurer?
    -> Player: Unhand those Familiars!
        Regiment Leader: Ha, ha, ha! 
        Regiment Leader: Why, aren't you a brave fool.
    -> Player: I'll let you past. Just let me and my Familiar go.
        Regiment Leader: Ha, ha, ha! 
        Regiment Leader: You think we'd actually let you go?
Regiment Leader: I'll make an example of you for everyone on this ship. 
Regiment Leader: Oh, and of course I'll take your Familiar too.
===

